<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="36" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="36">The locality we present here corresponds to the coordinates given in the paper, although these do not agree with the elevation also reported in the paper: 2150 m a.s.l. This is very close to the maximum altitude of the highest peaks of the Djurdjura Mountains, and much higher than the 935 m a.s.l. of Tizi Oumalou.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
